# Tiny Greenhouse XR — Cursor Rules

Always read `AI_CONTEXT.md` at the project root before helping with this project.
It contains the full architecture, current build state, formulas, and rubric mapping.

## Critical Rules

- `FeedbackManager` = zero game logic. Pure output only.
- `EaseScale` = spawn from 0. `ScalePop` = button pulse. Never swap.
- All XR interaction = XRSimpleInteractable button press. No physics grab.
- One scene only. No new scenes.
- XRI types must use fully qualified namespaces:
  `UnityEngine.XR.Interaction.Toolkit.Interactables.XRSimpleInteractable`
- Methods wired to UnityEvent must be `public`.
- No DOTween. All easing is coroutines.
- No Animator controllers for plant growth — use `GameObject.SetActive()`.

